name: Invesco Russell 1000 Dynamic-Multifactor Index ETF
longDescription: The ETF invests primarily in equity securities of US companies and currently holds securities of Invesco Russell 1000  Dynamic Multifactor ETF (Cboe BZX ticker: OMFL) in order to replicate the Russell 1000  Invesco Dynamic Multifactor Index. The index is comprised of securities from the 1000 largest US companies that are evaluated using specific investment factors which have historically performed well in the current stage of the economic cycle and which factors are adjusted as the economic cycle changes. IUMF seeks to replicate to the extent reasonably possible and before fees and expenses, the performance of the Russell 1 Invesco Dynamic Multifactor Index, or any successor thereto, on an unhedged basis, in the case of any unhedged units, or on a hedged basis, in the case of any hedged units.
